Reasoning: The paper deals with visual arts and proposes a framework based on deep convolutional neural networks for feature extraction and unsupervised nearest neighbor approach for visual link retrieval among digitized paintings. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves knowledge discovery, which suggests that it could also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of deep learning techniques for feature extraction and unsupervised learning suggests that the paper could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's use of graph analysis suggests that it could also belong to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
